"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-04-09-paris-2024-qualifier-super-falcons-hold-banyana-banyana-secure-olympics-ticket\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's Super Falcons secured a place at the 2024 Olympic Games after battling to a 0-0 draw against South Africa at the Loftus Versfeld Stadium, Pretoria, on Tuesday.  Randy Waldrum's side won the final qualifying round contest 1-0 on aggregate.  Nigeria carved out the first chance of the game with Kaylin Swart saving Chinwendu Ihezuo's cross.  The Super Falcons were in total control of the game in the first half, with the hosts struggling to create any clear cut opportunity.  Goalkeeper, Chiamaka Nnadozie needed to be at her twice to deny the South Africans in the second half.  EPL: They are worried - Ogden reveals fixture that could cost Liverpool title  NLO reads riot acts to clubs ahead of new season  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"